    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So that version would look like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">theorem</span> <span class=\"n\">LinearMap.singular_value_decomposition</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">T</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’â‚—</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"bp\">âˆƒ</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">â„•</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Ïƒ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Fin</span> <span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">â„</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hÏƒ</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ€</span> <span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">Ïƒ</span> <span class=\"n\">i</span> <span class=\"bp\">&gt;</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">v</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Fin</span> <span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">w</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Fin</span> <span class=\"n\">r</span> <span class=\"bp\">â†’</span> <span class=\"n\">W</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hv</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Orthonormal</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">v</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">hw</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">Orthonormal</span> <span class=\"bp\">ğ•œ</span> <span class=\"n\">w</span><span class=\"o\">),</span> <span class=\"n\">Antitone</span> <span class=\"n\">Ïƒ</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ§</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">T</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">hw.toIsometry</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ˜â‚—</span> <span class=\"n\">toLin'</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">diagonal</span> <span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"bp\">â†‘</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ˜</span> <span class=\"n\">Ïƒ</span><span class=\"o\">))</span> <span class=\"bp\">âˆ˜â‚—</span> <span class=\"n\">adjoint</span> <span class=\"n\">hv.toIsometry</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n  <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 393786263,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1695926888
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To be honest, in my version there is something that annoys me: we should be saying exactly what <code>Ïƒ</code> is (i.e., square roots of eigenvalues of <code>T.adjoint * T</code> listed in nonincreasing order), but I don't think we can do this yet because we don't have enough material about positive operators (my fault!).</p>",
        "id": 393786490,
